{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
Well, I [D]read up the last of my [G]letter
I [D]tore off the stamp for Black [A]Jim
When [G]Billy rode up to re[D]lieve me
He just [A]looked at my letter and [D]grinned
{end_of_verse}


{start_of_chorus: Chorus 1}
He said, now [G]why do they [A]ride for their [D]money
Tell me [G]why do they [A]rope for short [D]pay
